What is the purpose of a MAC address on an ethernet network????

- MAC Media Access Control - every device has a 12 char hexadecimal MAC address.
- Frames are transferred at layer2 - which contain layer address or MAC address
- Switch listens to all frames coming in & looks at source mac address, stores it in mac address table so it knows where to send that frame back.
- If they do not have/know a L2 address, it will broadcast/flood frame  on all other ports everywhere
- Learns, forwards, or floods (in order)

Example - remote port 10 sends frame to l2 switch, switch 2 look at source address in the incoming frame, stores it in MAC address table so that next time it needs to send a frame outbound, it will use port 10 as the destination address
